### TaskHub — HTTP request collection
# IntelliJ HTTP Client / VS Code "REST Client" format.
#
# Status of endpoints:
#   - /actuator/*  → available now (Session 1)
#   - /api/auth, /api/projects, /api/tasks, /api/tags, /api/users
#                  → built in Session 2 (REST + Security). Kept here so the
#                    contract is runnable the moment each slice lands.
#
# Flow: run "Register" (or you already have a user) → run "Login" to capture the
# JWT into {{token}} → every protected request below sends it automatically.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

# Set after running "Login" (auto-captured by the response handler below).
@token = {{auth_token}}


### ── Actuator (Session 1, works now) ────────────────────────────────────────

### Health
GET {{host}}/actuator/health

### Info
GET {{host}}/actuator/info

### Prometheus metrics
GET {{host}}/actuator/prometheus

### OpenAPI JSON (Session 2)
GET {{host}}/v3/api-docs


### ── Auth (Session 2) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register a new USER
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "S3cret!pass"
}

### Login — captures the JWT into {{auth_token}}
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "S3cret!pass"
}

> {%
    // Adjust the field name if the login response wraps the token differently.
    client.global.set("auth_token", response.body.token ?? response.body.accessToken);
%}


### ── Projects (Session 2) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List projects (paginated)
GET {{host}}/api/projects?page=0&size=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create a project
# @name createProject
POST {{host}}/api/projects
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Website Redesign",
  "description": "Q3 marketing site overhaul"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("projectId", response.body.id);
%}

### Get one project
GET {{host}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update a project
PUT {{host}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Website Redesign",
  "description": "Q3 marketing site overhaul — updated scope"
}

### Delete a project
DELETE {{host}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ── Tasks (Session 2) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List tasks in a project (paginated + filters)
GET {{host}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks?page=0&size=20&status=TODO
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create a task in a project
# @name createTask
POST {{host}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Draft homepage copy",
  "description": "First pass at hero + features sections",
  "status": "TODO",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "dueDate": "2026-08-01",
  "assigneeId": 1,
  "tagIds": [1, 2]
}

> {%
    client.global.set("taskId", response.body.id);
%}

### Get one task
GET {{host}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update a task (e.g. move to IN_PROGRESS)
PUT {{host}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Draft homepage copy",
  "description": "First pass at hero + features sections",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "dueDate": "2026-08-01",
  "assigneeId": 1,
  "tagIds": [1, 2]
}

### Delete a task
DELETE {{host}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ── Tags (Session 2) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List tags
GET {{host}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create a tag
POST {{host}}/api/tags
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "urgent",
  "color": "#e11d48"
}


### ── Users — ADMIN only (Session 2) ───────────────────────────────────────

### List users (requires ADMIN role)
GET {{host}}/api/users?page=0&size=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ── Negative / auth checks (Session 2) ───────────────────────────────────

### No token → expect 401
GET {{host}}/api/projects

### Malformed token → expect 401
GET {{host}}/api/projects
Authorization: Bearer not-a-real-token

### Validation error → expect 400 problem-JSON
POST {{host}}/api/projects
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": ""
}

### Unknown resource → expect 404 problem-JSON
GET {{host}}/api/projects/999999
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ── Task events over gRPC (Session 3) ────────────────────────────────────
#
# Every task mutation above (create / update / delete) is published to
# notification-service over gRPC once the transaction commits. The gRPC calls
# themselves live in `grpc.http` — subscribe there, then run the requests below and
# watch the events arrive.
#
# X-Correlation-Id is optional: supplied here it is echoed back on the response and
# propagated as gRPC metadata, so one action is traceable across both services' logs.
# Omit it and taskhub-api mints one for you.
#
# ── Watching the events with grpcurl ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Prefer the terminal to the IDE? These are the same calls. Needs `grpcurl` and `jq`,
# notification-service running on :9090, and reflection (on by default in dev).
#
#   TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST localhost:8080/api/auth/login \
#     -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
#     -d '{"username":"alice","password":"S3cret!pass"}' | jq -r .token)
#
# What does this server expose?
#
#   grpcurl -plaintext localhost:9090 list
#   grpcurl -plaintext localhost:9090 describe taskhub.notification.v1.NotificationService
#
# Subscribe and LEAVE IT RUNNING in its own terminal — project_id "0" = every project.
# (64-bit ids are quoted: proto3's JSON mapping renders int64 as a string.)
#
#   grpcurl -plaintext -H "authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -d '{"project_id": "0"}' \
#     localhost:9090 taskhub.notification.v1.NotificationService/SubscribeTaskEvents
#
# Now run the requests below. Each one prints an event on that stream, e.g.:
#
#   {"event_id":"a89335ae…","type":"TASK_CREATED","task_id":"16","project_id":"4",
#    "title":"Observe me over gRPC","status":"TODO","actor":"alice"}
#
# Publish an event by hand, without touching the REST API (`accepted: true` comes back;
# `delivered_to` counts the open subscriptions it reached, and is omitted when zero):
#
#   grpcurl -plaintext -H "authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H 'x-correlation-id: my-trace' \
#     -d '{"event_id":"manual-1","type":"TASK_CREATED","task_id":"1","project_id":"1",
#          "title":"Draft homepage copy","status":"TODO","actor":"alice"}' \
#     localhost:9090 taskhub.notification.v1.NotificationService/NotifyTaskEvent
#
# No token, or a forged one → the auth interceptor rejects it before the handler runs:
#
#   grpcurl -plaintext -d '{"event_id":"forged"}' \
#     localhost:9090 taskhub.notification.v1.NotificationService/NotifyTaskEvent
#   # ERROR: Code: Unauthenticated  Message: A valid bearer token is required
#
# Health is exempt, so probes keep working without a token → {"status":"SERVING"}:
#
#   grpcurl -plaintext localhost:9090 grpc.health.v1.Health/Check
#
# `grpc.http` has these as runnable IDE requests.

### Create a task → emits TASK_CREATED
POST {{host}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Correlation-Id: my-trace

{
  "title": "Observe me over gRPC",
  "description": "Watch this land on the SubscribeTaskEvents stream",
  "status": "TODO",
  "priority": "HIGH"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("eventTaskId", response.body.id);
%}

### Reassign it → emits TASK_ASSIGNED
PUT {{host}}/api/tasks/{{eventTaskId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Correlation-Id: my-trace

{
  "title": "Observe me over gRPC",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "assigneeId": 1
}

### Finish it → emits TASK_COMPLETED (completion wins over reassignment)
PUT {{host}}/api/tasks/{{eventTaskId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Correlation-Id: my-trace

{
  "title": "Observe me over gRPC",
  "status": "DONE",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "assigneeId": 1
}

### Delete it → emits TASK_DELETED
DELETE {{host}}/api/tasks/{{eventTaskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-Correlation-Id: my-trace
